commit_message:
Add engine preview stack with Template and Params

Add support for the engine to return the preview of a stack given a
template and the necessary parameters.  No resource will actually be
created, just returned for visualization purposes.  This allows a user
to know beforehand what will happen to their stacks once they used such
template.

The response is a formatted stack plus formatted resources in it:

  {
      'stack': {
        // stack information similar to a call to stack_create/show
        'resources': [
            // resources similar to a call to resource_show
        ]
      }
  }

For now, grouped resources (any of the StackResource) will just be
returned as a single resource, but the preview will be overridden in the
future to allow for more specific behavior.

Implements: blueprint preview-stack (partial)
Change-Id: I8b862110f00ac0cf31d96a86cbc134df895cc19b

Adding required parameters for trove taskmanager

Reasons:
 - not each instance with predefined datastore could reach active state
   during default usage_timeout (300 seconds);
 - update_status_on_fail should be true to avoid stacked instances;
 - usage_sleep_time should be changed to avoid hammering the
   database every second for 5+ minutes.
Changes:
 - update_status_on_fail = True;
 - usage_sleep_time = 5;
 - usage_timeout = 500;

